Commander Genius (https://www.portmaster.games) 
===============================================

Original version by:

- Gerhard Stein https://github.com/gerstrong/Commander-Genius

Portmaster Version: 	

- tob10 https://github.com/tobio-tenma
- Christian Haitian https://github.com/christianhaitian

Description:
============

Commander Genius is an open-source clone of Commander Keen (Episodes 1-6, Dreams) which allows you
to play these episodes and some of the mods and additional community content made for them.
Developed by Gerstrong and originally ported by Christian Haitian.

Instructions:
=============

Includes all of the officially released free content for Commander Keen: the shareware versions
(Episodes 1 and 4), and the demo versions (Episode 6 and Keen Dreams). You can add load your own
game file directories into the 'ports/cgenius/.CommanderGenius/games' folder or, if you have an
internet connection on-device, you can download additional community created content directly from
the launcher ('More+' button near bottom of screen).

To Compile:
===========

# binary will be located 'CGeniusBuild/src/CGeniusExe' when complete
git clone https://gitlab.com/Dringgstein/Commander-Genius.git
mkdir CGeniusBuild && cd CGeniusBuild
cmake ../Commander-Genius/
make

Controls:
=============
Start       = Exit to main menu
Select      = Display status
D-pad       = Move character
A Button    = Jump
B Button    = Shoot blaster
Y Button    = Toggle pogo stick on/off

Note: Default controls are shown, however there is support to remap to preference. Done once
in-game (any episode) but, once complete, the new mapping is applies globally.